; tube (rocket launcher, one shot only.)

INUMBER 892
NAME 648
WEIGHT 5
VOLUME 3
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
BOW_WEAPON
PARAMETER1 32000

*DESCRIPTION_START
You see a tube about the length of you arm, and several inches in diameter.
Some instructions are written along the lenght of it.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB READ -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You glance over the instructions:
  ECHO PLAYER %cHDP - High Damage Projectile.
  ECHO PLAYER Step 1: Flip out the safety pin.
  ECHO PLAYER Step 2: Pull out the inner tube and lock it into position.
  ECHO PLAYER Step 3: Ready weapon and aim.
  ECHO PLAYER Step 4: Fire.	
  ECHO PLAYER Step 5: Discard.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB FLIP -1
IFVAR ITEMBIT2 = 0
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 0
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
    ECHO PLAYER You tug on the safety pin and pull it clear of the housing.
    ECHO OTHERS %n tugs on the safety pin and pulls it clear of the housing on %a.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL A round cover at each end of the tube falls to the ground, revealing a hollow tube with a medium sized projectile inside.
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The safety pin has already been released.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL -1
IFVAR ITEMBIT2 = 0
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
    IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 0
      CLEARVERB
      EQUAL ITEMBIT1 1
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
      ECHO PLAYER You pull out the inner tube, extending it to its full length and lock it into place.
      ECHO OTHERS %n pulls out the inner tube, extending %a to its full length and locks it into place.
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1
      EQUAL ITEMBIT2 1
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The tube is already extended.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can not extend the tube without releasing the safety pin first.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
ENDIF

; duelling pistols

INUMBER 896
NAME 159
WEIGHT 4
VOLUME 4
HANDGUN

*DESCRIPTION_START
You see a fancy hand held pistol. A titanium barrel is connected to a
polished, hand carved wooden stock that flows, rather then bends.
You see a small titanium hammer protruding from the back and a titanium
hammer and guard underneath.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB LOOK -1
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER **  Archnum not to be use by order of Kreebonker the Godly.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH -1
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
  ECHO PLAYER You cock the hammer.
  ECHO OTHERS %n cocks the hammer.
ENDIF

VARIABLE DUELROOM1
VARIABLE DUELFIRE1
IFPREVERB PULL -1
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
    EQUAL DUELROOM1 RNUM
    IFSEEK 979
     IFITEM -1 WIELDED
     IFVAR BODYPOINTS > 0
      IFVAR DUELROOM1 = RNUM
        EQUAL DUELFIRE1 1
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR DUELFIRE1 = 1
        SKILLCHECK 3 -245 DUMMY1
        IFVAR DUMMY1 > 0
          IFSEEK 979
            CLEARVERB
            EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
            DAMAGEPLR BODYONLY 5000 You get drilled right between the eyes.
            ECHO OTHERS %n gets drilled right between the eyes.
            GMMSG %N got shot.
            EQUAL DUELFIRE1 0
            EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
          ENDIF
        ELSE
          CLEARVERB
          EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
          ECHO PLAYER %cYou fire and miss.
          ECHO OTHERS %n fires and misses.
          EQUAL DUELFIRE1 0
          EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
        ENDIF
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Shoot at who?
      EQUAL DUELFIRE1 0
    ENDIF
 ELSE
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You pull the trigger and nothing happens. Try cocking the hammer by pushing it back.
 ENDIF
ENDIF


