;
;
;Rules
INUMBER 1126
NAME 694
ARTICLE the
MISC
WEIGHT 1000
SUBSTANCE INDESTRUCTABLE
HIDDEN

IFPREVERB EXAM -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER The Rules item is used to display the rules for the Virtual Cafe games. So
      ECHO PLAYER far we only have rules for Trivia and High Five. Simply TURN the rules until
      ECHO PLAYER they are displaying for the right game.
   ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER Why don't you try reading them?
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TURN -1
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ADD ITEMVAL1 1
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
         EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
         ECHO PLAYER Set to display Trivia Rules.
         GMMSG %N turned the rules to display for Trivia.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
         ECHO PLAYER Set to display High Five Rules.
         GMMSG %N turned the rules to display for High Five.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
         ECHO PLAYER We don't need no stinkin' rulez!
         GMMSG %N turned the rules to display "no game"
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ -1
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
      ECHO PLAYER There is currently no Virtual Cafe game being hosted here. For a listing of
      ECHO PLAYER Games and other Events, check the Virtual Cafe Calendar.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      ECHO PLAYER  Here are the rules for Virtual Cafe Trivia...%c
      ECHO PLAYER      Welcome to Virtual Cafe Trivia, written by Mark J. Sloop for Novalink.
      ECHO PLAYER                 Copyright 1994, Inner Circle Technologies, Inc.%c
      ECHO PLAYER  Each round a question will be displayed and you will have from 30 - 90 seconds
      ECHO PLAYER  to WHISPER your answer to the Trivia Host. You will be informed whether or not
      ECHO PLAYER  your answer is correct. Scores for each round are based on the total number of
      ECHO PLAYER  answers received divided by the total number of CORRECT answers. So if two out
      ECHO PLAYER  four players are correct, each receives two points. The Trivia Host determines
      ECHO PLAYER  how much time you are given to answer the question.%c
      ECHO PLAYER  If Carry Over mode is being used, whenever there are no correct answers, bonus
      ECHO PLAYER  points equal to the number of incorrect answers are "carried over" to the next
      ECHO PLAYER  round, to be divided between the players who get the next round correct. If no
      ECHO PLAYER  one answers the next question, the "carried over" points are forfeited.%c
      ECHO PLAYER  Please do not say your answer OUT LOUD. Whisper your answer to the Trivia Host
      ECHO PLAYER  who is running the game. And please do not cheat by whispering the answer to a
      ECHO PLAYER  friend. That only ruins the game for others.%c
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
      ECHO PLAYER  Here are the rules for High Five...%c
      ECHO PLAYER           Welcome to High Five, written by Mark J. Sloop for NovaLink.
      ECHO PLAYER                  Copyright 1994, Inner Circle Technologies, Inc.%c
      ECHO PLAYER  The object of High Five is to try to get the best possible combination of five
      ECHO PLAYER  six-sided dice, like the game Yahtzee. The best POSSIBLE combination is a five
      ECHO PLAYER  of a kind, or a High Five! You are allowed to roll your dice twice each round,
      ECHO PLAYER  but you get bonus points for each UNUSED roll.%c
      ECHO PLAYER             The different dice combinations are scored as follows...%c
      ECHO PLAYER    High Five (5 of a Kind) .............................. 100 + Total of Dice
      ECHO PLAYER    Large Straight ....................................... 80
      ECHO PLAYER    4 of a Kind .......................................... 60 + Total of Dice
      ECHO PLAYER    Small Straight ....................................... 45
      ECHO PLAYER    Full House ........................................... 35
      ECHO PLAYER    3 of a Kind .......................................... 20 + Total of Dice
      ECHO PLAYER    2 Pairs .............................................. 10 + Total of Dice
      ECHO PLAYER    1 Pair ...............................................  5 + Total of Dice
      ECHO PLAYER    Zilcho ...............................................      Total of Dice%c
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB BREAK -1
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER Did you really think you'd be allowed to break the rules?
   ECHO OTHERS %N tried to break the rules, and failed!
ENDIF
