VARIABLE DEMONCAN
VARIABLE DEMONSPL

INUMBER 995
NAME 500
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
*DESCRIPTION_START
The candle is a length of black wax, tapering to a wick of some kind of hair
at one end. It seems never to have been lit, for none of the wax has melted in
any way. Runes have been carefully etched along its entire length, spelling out
several simple phrases and names in a language you can... almost... understand.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB LIGHT -1
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR DEMONCAN ! 0
		ECHO PLAYER The candle will not light again for some time, you sense.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR DEMONCAN = 0
		ADD DEMONCAN 1
		EQUAL DEMONSPL 326
		RANDOM DUMMY1 1 7 0
		ADD DEMONSPL DUMMY1
		ECHO OTHERS %N lights %a, which flares for a moment, then goes out, its wick and wax completely untouched.
		ECHO PLAYER You light %a, which flares for a moment, then goes out, its wick and wax completely untouched.
		EQUAL ITEMVAL2 20
		EQUAL ITEMVAL3 DEMONSPL
		ROUTINE 1
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER GM: This candle can be lit three or four times a day, and does a random statistic-increase spell when it does. It will never run out.
	ENDIF
ENDIF

