*DESCRIPTION_START EXAM
The blowgun is made from a six foot long bamboo shoot. It's outer surface has
been coated with a hard, waxy substance to prevent loss of any air pressure.
A sack of stitched lizardskin hangs from the blowhole of the weapon and seems
to contain a liquid of some sort.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB WIELD -1
 ECHO PLAYER You raise the blowgun to your mouth.
 ECHO OTHERS %n raises a blowgun to %h mouth.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH -1
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 1
   CLEARVERB
   ADD ITEMVAL5 1
   IFVAR ITEMVAL5 <= 200
    ECHO PLAYER You reach up and squeeze the lizardskin sack and hear the liquid squirt into the shaft.
    ECHO OTHERS %n reaches up to a lizardskin sack hanging from the blowhole of %h blowgun and gently squeezes it.
    RANDOM ITEMVAL1 1 100 0
    IFVAR ITEMVAL1 <= 60
     EQUAL ITEMVAL4 75
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You squeeze the lizardskin sack but do not hear any of the liquid eject into the pole.
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER The blowgun is not loaded.
   CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF

INUMBER 687
NAME 524
WEIGHT 2
VOLUME 3
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 2
WORN_WRIST
PUNCTURE_WEAPON
OPENABLE

IFPREVERB PUSH -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER The steel spike in the cane is already extended.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER Applying the slightest pressure to the knobbed end of the cane, you flash a malicious grin as a half foot spike of cold, deadly steel snaps out from the base!
  ECHO OTHERS %n fiddles with the cane and a half foot spike of cold, deadly steel snaps from the base!
  EQUAL ITEMVAL5 1
  EQUAL ITEMADJ1 554
  EQUAL ITEMADJ2 590
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WIELD -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL5 ! 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The cane cannot be wielded like this.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TAP -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You push the spike back into the cane by firmly rapping it on the ground.
  ECHO OTHERS %n pushes the spike back inside the cane by firmly rapping it on the ground.
  EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
  EQUAL ITEMADJ1 -1
  EQUAL ITEMADJ2 -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
 ECHO PLAYER You flip the crook of the cane up, revealing a small cavity.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER *** Auction Item - PUSH and TAP to work. ***
  ECHO PLAYER ***  Zyphyni, UID WABBIT. May, 1995 ***
 ENDIF
ENDIF

INUMBER 688
NAME 393
LIQUID
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
SUBSTANCE INSUBSTANTIAL
ARTICLE SOME
IFPREVERB PINCH -1
 CLEARVERB
 ROUTINE 1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER There is only sand enough for one final pinch remaining.
 ENDIF
 IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 0
  ECHO PLAYER You use the final pinch of sand.
  REMOVEITEM -1
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You take a pinch of the sand and sprinkle it over your head.
  ECHO OTHERS %n lifts %h hand above %h head and sprinkles a glittering shower of sand across %h shoulders.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DRINK -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER It's sand, do normal, sane people DRINK sand?
ENDIF
;
;meep
INUMBER 338
NAME 1023
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a small clockwork creature, about the size of a rabbit. Its body is egg-shaped, supported by four long spindly spider-like legs; it is half-covered by a patch of colored plush, and underneath you can see whirring gold and silver gears. It has bright black eyes, and a black button nose, and no ears to speak of.
*DESCRIPTION_END
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 1
MISC
WORN_HEAD
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
IFPREVERB PINCH -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You pinch your meep, and it says, "Yeep! Meep!"
	ECHO OTHERS %N's meep says, "Yeep! Meep!"
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WAVE -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER Your meep hops wildly about you, colliding with things.
	ECHO OTHERS %N's meep hops wildly about %i, banging off walls and floors alarmingly.
ENDIF
IFVERB GAZE -1
	ECHO PLAYER Your meep gazes at you with love and adoration in its bright black eyes.
	ECHO OTHERS %N's meep gazes at %i with love and affection.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PET -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You pet %a.
	ECHO OTHERS %N pets %a.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You push your meep off your lap, and it tries to jump back up.
	ECHO OTHERS %N pushes %h sad-looking meep off %h lap, and it tries to jump back up.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You pull your meep onto your lap, and it snuggles in, making little purring and beeping noises.
	ECHO OTHERS %N pulls %h meep onto %h lap, and it snuggles in, making little purring and beeping noises.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You shine and polish your meep's gears.
	ECHO OTHERS %N shines and polishes %h meep's gears.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB KISS -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You kiss your meep on its black button nose!
	ECHO OTHERS %N kisses %h meep on its black button nose!
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUNCH -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You punch your meep, and it explodes into a billion tiny gears.
	ECHO OTHERS %N drives %h fist through %h meep, and it explodes into a billion tiny gears and fragments.
	REMOVEITEM -1
ENDIF
IFPREVERB KICK -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER Your kick fragments your meep into tiny gears and pieces!
	ECHO OTHERS %N's meep explodes into tiny gears and pieces as %s kicks it!
	REMOVEITEM -1
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PLAY -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER Your meep meeps menacingly and pounces on a stray piece of trash.
	ECHO OTHERS %N's meep meeps menacingly and pounces on a stray piece of trash.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB HUG -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER As you hug your meep close, it sniffs your ear and meeps lovingly.
	ECHO OTHERS As %N hugs %a, it meeps lovingly and sniffs %h ear.
ENDIF
